{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nCreation provenance stops being auditable if compaction retires the original CREATE and the replacement SNAPSHOT omits or reinterprets the channel. This story makes recorded, inferred, and unknown provenance durable across normal compaction, conservative-horizon compaction, SNAPSHOT-only replay, legacy snapshots, and snapshot rebuild/recovery.\n\n## What\n\n- Preserve creation_channel and the optional true-only creation_channel_inferred marker inside SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state. Do not add them to the SNAPSHOT envelope, whose author/env_id identify the compactor.\n- Confirm src/rebar/_commands/compact.py continues to copy the complete reduced state while stripping only updated_at and the legacy signature mirror. Add a contract test that calls _snapshot_strip_keys() and asserts its result is disjoint from {\"creation_channel\", \"creation_channel_inferred\"}. The guard is deliberately test-enforced rather than a production assertion because the strip set is static internal policy and CI is the enforcement boundary.\n- Document the rollback schema-state matrix: an existing new-code SNAPSHOT retains unknown compiled_state keys through old-code recompaction; a first old-code compaction of raw creation-bearing CREATE events omits the field and loses it if those CREATEs retire; a never-compacted ticket retains the raw CREATE value while the old reader hides it. The supported back-out retains the new reader/compactor. A full binary downgrade must pause compaction/event retirement until the feature returns, or verify that new-code SNAPSHOTs already contain the field for all affected tickets.\n- After process_snapshot restores compiled_state, run the same legacy projection helper used after CREATE only when creation_channel is absent. A legacy snapshot with jira-* ticket_id plus reconciler author/env_id becomes inferred jira; every other legacy snapshot becomes unknown. A snapshot carrying a recorded channel is restored verbatim and never re-inferred.\n- Materialize creation_channel_inferred=true into snapshots produced from inferred historical state so later SNAPSHOT-only replay retains the certainty marker without access to retired CREATE files.\n- Cover rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log and partial-horizon compaction, including replay of live events after the snapshot.\n- Update event/compaction documentation to state that ticket genesis provenance lives in compiled_state and is distinct from SNAPSHOT event authorship. Update docs/output-schemas.md to state that SNAPSHOT-only replay plus snapshot rebuild emit the same creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred values through show/list/search/export as full-log replay.\n\n## Approach Rationale\n\nThe compactor already snapshots reducer output and process_snapshot restores every compiled-state key. Preserving the field through that established path avoids a second provenance representation and keeps normal replay and recovery identical. A small legacy migration hook after snapshot restore is necessary because pre-feature snapshots cannot contain the new keys. No event rewrite or snapshot format fork is required. The rollback guidance distinguishes safe carry-forward of keys already present in compiled_state from the unsafe first-compaction case; that explicit boundary prevents the generic unknown-key preservation behavior from being overstated.\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: normal and horizon compaction, SNAPSHOT-only replay, legacy SNAPSHOT fallback, snapshot rebuild/recovery, field-retention guards, the full-downgrade schema-state/precondition matrix, and compaction documentation.\n\nOUT: changing source_event_uuids semantics, changing SNAPSHOT envelope authorship, rewriting existing snapshots, changing compaction thresholds, or adding a store-format migration.\n\n## Files\n\n- src/rebar/_commands/compact.py: compiled-state retention and rebuild path.\n- src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py: post-SNAPSHOT legacy projection using the shared helper.\n- tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py: end-to-end retirement and replay.\n- tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py: direct recorded/inferred/unknown snapshot projection.\n- tests/integration/test_concurrency_regression.py: rebuild and horizon regression where needed.\n- docs/event-schema.md and docs/concurrency.md: SNAPSHOT placement and recovery semantics.\n- docs/output-schemas.md: consumer-facing parity between full-log, SNAPSHOT-only, and rebuilt-SNAPSHOT replay.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on the Jira/import story because the shared field, inference helper, and marker semantics must exist before snapshot migration can preserve them.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Compacting tickets recorded as cli, mcp, python, jira, and import writes the exact channel into SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state, retires the source CREATE, and SNAPSHOT-only replay returns the same value without an inference marker. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k recorded.\n- [ ] Compacting an inferred historical Jira ticket materializes creation_channel=jira and creation_channel_inferred=true in compiled_state; SNAPSHOT-only replay preserves both. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k inferred.\n- [ ] A pre-feature SNAPSHOT lacking both keys projects inferred Jira only for the exact three-signal predicate and otherwise unknown, while a SNAPSHOT carrying any recorded channel bypasses inference. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py -k creation_channel.\n- [ ] creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred never appear on the SNAPSHOT envelope and are not removed by _snapshot_strip_keys. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k placement.\n- [ ] rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log and conservative-horizon compaction preserve the same provenance while later live events replay normally. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"rebuild or horizon\" tests/integration/test_concurrency_regression.py.\n- [ ] Existing snapshot consistency, rollback recovery, and forward-compat behavior remain green. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_compact_rollback_recovery.py tests/interfaces/store/test_fsck_snapshot_checks.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_event_schema_forward_compat.py.\n- [ ] docs/output-schemas.md documents full-log/SNAPSHOT output parity, and docs/concurrency.md documents the three post-rollback schema states plus the full-downgrade compaction/event-retirement pause or new-code-SNAPSHOT precondition. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784261992091658001,"uuid":"a47c81d5-3449-48ff-817b-8fc248e549f4"}